<subSubSection lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="360" pageId="8" pageNumber="359" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1604,2024]" pageId="8" pageNumber="359">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1783,1808]" pageId="8" pageNumber="359">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Due to the long ocelloccipital distance, which is about 2.5x as long as the ocellar diameter (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 15–20. 15–18" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1427,1450]" captionTargetBox="[152,1432,493,1401]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[149,1434,491,1404]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 15–20. 15–18:Haetosmia pakistaniensis. 15: Female in lateral view.16: Vertex of female. 17: Proboscis of female. 18: Antenna of male. 19–20:Haetosmia vechti. 19: Genitalia of male in ventral view. 20:Sterna 4–6 of male." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1068120/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="359">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
), the female of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Müller &amp; Griswold" authorityYear="2017" box="[367,562,1820,1845]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Haetosmia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="359" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pakistaniensis">
<emphasis box="[367,562,1820,1845]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="359">H. pakistaniensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be confounded only with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1974" box="[916,1020,1820,1845]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Haetosmia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="359" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vechti">
<emphasis box="[916,1020,1820,1845]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="359">H. vechti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Compared to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1974" box="[1194,1298,1820,1845]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Haetosmia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="359" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vechti">
<emphasis box="[1194,1298,1820,1845]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="359">H. vechti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the second segment of the labial palpus of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Müller &amp; Griswold" authorityYear="2017" box="[504,698,1855,1880]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Haetosmia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="359" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pakistaniensis">
<emphasis box="[504,698,1855,1880]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="359">H. pakistaniensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is only about 1.8x as long as the first segment (2.3x as long in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1974" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Haetosmia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="359" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vechti">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="359">H. vechti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the capitate pollen-harvesting bristles cover the entire length of the second segment of the labial palpus (
<figureCitation box="[159,243,1927,1952]" captionStart="FIGURES 15–20. 15–18" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1427,1450]" captionTargetBox="[152,1432,493,1401]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[149,1434,491,1404]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 15–20. 15–18:Haetosmia pakistaniensis. 15: Female in lateral view.16: Vertex of female. 17: Proboscis of female. 18: Antenna of male. 19–20:Haetosmia vechti. 19: Genitalia of male in ventral view. 20:Sterna 4–6 of male." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1068120/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="359">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
; only the apical two thirds or less in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1974" box="[669,772,1927,1952]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Haetosmia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="359" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vechti">
<emphasis box="[669,772,1927,1952]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="359">H. vechti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), these bristles are as long as or longer than the maxillary palpus (
<figureCitation box="[239,322,1964,1989]" captionStart="FIGURES 15–20. 15–18" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1427,1450]" captionTargetBox="[152,1432,493,1401]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[149,1434,491,1404]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 15–20. 15–18:Haetosmia pakistaniensis. 15: Female in lateral view.16: Vertex of female. 17: Proboscis of female. 18: Antenna of male. 19–20:Haetosmia vechti. 19: Genitalia of male in ventral view. 20:Sterna 4–6 of male." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1068120/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="359">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
; shorter than the maxillary palpus in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1974" box="[738,839,1964,1989]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Haetosmia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="359" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vechti">
<emphasis box="[738,839,1964,1989]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="359">H. vechti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and the white appressed pilosity on vertex and terga is more strongly developed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Müller &amp; Griswold" authorityYear="2017" box="[495,689,1999,2024]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Haetosmia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="359" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pakistaniensis">
<emphasis box="[495,689,1999,2024]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="359">H. pakistaniensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[705,789,1999,2024]" captionStart="FIGURES 15–20. 15–18" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1427,1450]" captionTargetBox="[152,1432,493,1401]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[149,1434,491,1404]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 15–20. 15–18:Haetosmia pakistaniensis. 15: Female in lateral view.16: Vertex of female. 17: Proboscis of female. 18: Antenna of male. 19–20:Haetosmia vechti. 19: Genitalia of male in ventral view. 20:Sterna 4–6 of male." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1068120/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="359">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
). The male of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Müller &amp; Griswold" authorityYear="2017" box="[955,1149,1999,2024]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Haetosmia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="359" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pakistaniensis">
<emphasis box="[955,1149,1999,2024]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="359">H. pakistaniensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also very similar to 
<emphasis box="[1409,1436,2001,2024]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="359">H.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,151,2013]" pageId="9" pageNumber="360">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1974" box="[151,218,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Haetosmia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="360" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vechti">
<emphasis box="[151,218,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="360">vechti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
including sternal characters and genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[699,830,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 15–20. 15–18" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1427,1450]" captionTargetBox="[152,1432,493,1401]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[149,1434,491,1404]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 15–20. 15–18:Haetosmia pakistaniensis. 15: Female in lateral view.16: Vertex of female. 17: Proboscis of female. 18: Antenna of male. 19–20:Haetosmia vechti. 19: Genitalia of male in ventral view. 20:Sterna 4–6 of male." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1068120/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="360">Figs 19, 20</figureCitation>
). However, the second segment of the labial palpus of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Müller &amp; Griswold" authorityYear="2017" box="[151,344,188,213]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Haetosmia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="360" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pakistaniensis">
<emphasis box="[151,344,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="360">H. pakistaniensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is only about 1.8x as long as the first segment (2.3x as long in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1974" box="[1047,1148,188,213]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Haetosmia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="360" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vechti">
<emphasis box="[1047,1148,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="360">H. vechti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the proboscis is slightly shorter not reaching in repose beyond the coxa of the foreleg (reaching the base or middle of the trochanter in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1974" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Haetosmia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="360" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vechti">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="360">H. vechti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the distance between the lateral ocellus and the preoccipital ridge is about 
<date box="[1065,1093,260,284]" pageId="9" pageNumber="360">2x</date>
as long as the ocellar diameter (1.6–1.9x as long in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1974" box="[394,498,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Haetosmia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="360" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vechti">
<emphasis box="[394,498,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="360">H. vechti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and the marginal zone of tergum 5 is completely black (yellowish-brown in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1974" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Haetosmia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="360" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vechti">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="360">H. vechti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
